# PR Body Hygiene v1.3

## Intent
Standardize PR bodies across repos using the canonical format:
Why / What changed / Risk / Checks / Links / Connected PRs / Staging Merge Gate / Test Results.

This task is documentation hygiene only.
Do NOT change code.

## No-invention rule
- Do not invent links, outcomes, test commands, or staging details.
- If a required link or detail is missing, write `TBD`.

## Packet discovery
Prefer PR packets stored under `docs/pr/`.

Use this order:
1) `docs/pr/PR-*/AGENTPACK.md`
2) `pr/PR-*/AGENTPACK.md`
3) `docs/pr/PR-*/INPUT.md`, `CHECKLIST.md`, `FIXLOG.md`
4) `pr/PR-*/INPUT.md`, `CHECKLIST.md`, `FIXLOG.md`
5) Fallback filename patterns anywhere:
   - `INPUT-PR-*.md`
   - `CHECKLIST-PR-*.md`
   - `FIXLOG-PR-*.md`

If multiple candidates match, choose highest PR number then newest modified file.
If unsure, stop and ask for the packet folder path.

## Apply-to-GitHub behavior
If GitHub CLI (`gh`) is available and authenticated:
- Update PR bodies via `gh pr edit ... --body-file ...`.
- If the PR is in another repo, use `gh pr edit ... -R <owner/repo>`.
Otherwise:
- Output final PR body text for manual paste.
